KARGO INSTALLATION

1.Install the Cert Manager by using Below Command
helm install cert-manager cert-manager \
  --repo https://charts.jetstack.io \
  --version 1.14.5 \
  --namespace cert-manager \
  --create-namespace \
  --set installCRDs=true \
  --wait


2.Installation of kargo
   Install htpasswd
     sudo apt update -y
     sudo apt install apache2-utils -y

   Use below Command to set your custom admin password i.e bcrypt format
     htpasswd -nbBC 10 "" admin123 | tr -d ':\n'
   Use below Command to generate the account token
     openssl rand -hex 32

   Now install kargo by using below command
   helm install kargo \
  oci://ghcr.io/akuity/kargo-charts/kargo \
  --version 1.0.4 \
  --namespace kargo \
  --create-namespace \
  --set api.service.type=ClusterIP \
  --set api.adminAccount.passwordHash='BCRYPT_GENERATED_PASSWORD' \
  --set api.adminAccount.tokenSigningKey='BCRYPT_ACCOUNT_TOKEN' \
  --wait


   NOW ADD ALL OTHER FILES SUCH AS ENVOY-CONFIG MAP, ENVOY-DEPLOYMENT, ENVOY-SERVICE FILE AS U CAN SEE IN THE OTHER FILES

     




